[[File:Fetuses of two cats- FMVZ USP-01.jpg|thumb|Fetuses of two cats.]] '''Felinology''' is the [[Research|study]] of [[cat]]s.<ref>As noted in the [[University of Belgrade]]'s Faculty of Veterinary Medicine [http://www.vfs.unsa.ba/ba_docs/desavanja/workshop_bologna_2007/7a_Beograd.ppt Curriculum]</ref> The term is of [[Latin]]-[[Greek language|Greek]] origin and comes from the Latin word ''{{lang|la|felinus}}'' (of cats, feline) and the Greek ''{{lang|grc|-logos}}'' (science). Felinology is concerned with studying the [[anatomy]], [[genetics]], [[physiology]], and [[animal husbandry|breeding]] of domestic and wild cats.
